[size=4]⚠️ [color=#cc0000][b][u]WARNING[/u][/b][/color][/size]
You must update Cyberpunk 2077 to the latest version on Steam to install this list.

[color=#5cbdcf][size=5][b][u]What is Chrome & Blood?[/u][/b][/size][/color]
[b]Chrome & Blood[/b] is a full overhaul of [i]Cyberpunk 2077[/i] for players who want a faster, harder, and more rewarding Night City. Combat, AI, economy, hacking, cyberware, stealth — all of it has been reworked. Builds matter, fights are lethal, and nothing is handed to you.

[color=#5cbdcf][size=5][b][u]Two Profiles, One List[/u][/b][/size][/color]
You pick your experience when you launch. Same deadly core, different rules.

[b][u][size=3]Immersive Profile[/size][/u][/b]
The hardcore option. Stripped down, survival-focused, and built around earning everything.
[list]
[*]Darker visuals, needs management, and UI restrictions via [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/16300][i]Dark Future[/i][/url][/*]
[*]HUD elements like the minimap, 3rd person driving, and health bars are locked behind cyberware through [i][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/21916]Immersive Cyberware[/url][/i][/*]
[*]Remaining HUD elements stay hidden unless the situation calls for them via [i][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/2592]Limited HUD[/url][/i][/*]
[*]In-game deliveries take time instead of being instant with [i][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/21482?tab=files]Virtual Atelier Delivery[/url][/i][/*]
[/list]


[b][u][size=3]Standard Profile[/size][/u][/b]
Same reworked combat and systems, just without the survival layer.
[list]
[*]Full UI and inventory access from the start[/*]
[*]No cyberpsychosis or humanity system[/*]
[*]No needs or HUD restrictions[/*]
[/list]


[b][u][size=3]Cosmetics[/size][/u][/b]
As of v3.2, cosmetic mods have been pulled from both profiles. Chrome & Blood is purely gameplay now so you can add whatever cosmetics you want on top. Use the [b][NoDelete][/b] tag in MO2 to keep your additions safe across updates.

[color=#5cbdcf][size=4][b][u]What Both Profiles Include[/u][/b][/size][/color]
[list]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Frameworks:[/color][/b] CET, redscript, RED4ext, ArchiveXL, TweakXL, Codeware, Mod Settings. everything you need is already set up.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Visuals:[/color][/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/20808]ReLUX[/url], [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/12490]Nova City 2[/url], [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/29190]Nova Optics[/url], HDR LUTs, upgraded civilians, and tuned weather/LOD/fog.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Combat:[/color][/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/31402]Much Better AI[/url], [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/30585]Cyber Enemies[/url], and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/2217]Lifepath Bonuses & Gang-Corp Traits[/url] form the new foundation. Enemies coordinate, use new cyberware abilities, and fight according to faction traits. Each faction is immune to exactly one damage type, status effect, or quickhack category.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Time Dilation:[/color][/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/4931]Time Dilation Overhaul[/url] reworks nearly every aspect of time dilation, with new Sandevistans and attunements that each play differently.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Weapons:[/color][/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/22819]Chrome Ballistics[/url] and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/21865]Damage Scaling and Balance - Extended[/url] make every weapon type — guns, blades, cyberware, hacks — worth building around. Modded weapons are level-gated and seeded onto enemies.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Cyberware:[/color][/b] Realistic slot limits and humanity costs. Powered by [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/19798]Neuralware - Chipware Expansion[/url] and the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/23554]Cyberware Improved[/url] series.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Perks:[/color][/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/26751]Merc Protocol – Perk Gameplay Expansion[/url] adds 18 new perks with unique mechanics built for this list.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Vehicles:[/color][/b] Reworked handling, [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/20675]Nitrous[/url], and a full garage of lore-friendly cars and bikes through [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/4454]Virtual Car Dealer[/url].[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Stealth & Hacking:[/color][/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/31402]Much Better AI[/url] makes enemies investigate noise, react to bodies and takedowns, search your last known position, and coordinate after spotting you. Enemy netrunners reposition and support their squad, while [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/27237]Much Better Netrunning[/url] overhauls hacking from the ground up.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Immersion:[/color][/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/15460]Immersive Fixers[/url], [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/21807]ammo limits[/url], [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/21820]bounty hunting[/url]﻿, longer day/night cycles, and better ripperdocs all add depth to how the world feels.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Economy:[/color][/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/30532]Gigs, loot, and rewards[/url]﻿ have been rebalanced through Much Better Eddies, my own economy overhaul built for this list.[/*]
[*][b][color=#45e0e0]Builds:[/color][/b] Dozens of weapon and cyberware mods give you real options no matter how you play.[/*]
[/list]

[color=#5cbdcf][size=4][b][u]The Bottom Line[/u][/b][/size][/color]
This list isn't meant to be easy. With all of the above mods tuned for [b]very hard[/b], in Chrome & Blood's Night City, [b]survival isn't a right — it's earned.[/b]

[i][color=#cc0000][b]Live Hard. Die Chrome.[/b][/color][/i]

