[color=#5cbdcf][b][u][size=4]System Requirements[/size][/u][/b][/color]
Based on internal testing and community feedback. Your mileage will vary depending on hardware, background programs, and drivers.

[color=#5cbdcf][b][u][size=4]Requirements[/size][/u][/b][/color]
[list]
[*]You must own an [b]official copy of Cyberpunk 2077[/b][/*]
[*]An [b]SSD is required[/b] — HDD installs will crash and have texture issues[/*]
[*]Only [b]Windows 10/11[/b] is supported. I [b]will not[/b] provide support for Linux or other OSes.[/*]
[/list]


[url=https://ibb.co/ZRNRJh6P][img]https://i.ibb.co/FknkWBbM/system-requirements.png[/img][/url]

[list]
[*]Base Game & DLC: ~84.6 GB[/*]
[*]Modlist Download Size: ~11 GB[/*]
[*]Modlist Install Size: ~9.6 GB[/*]
[*][b]MODLIST TOTAL: ~21 GB[/b][/*]
[*][b]OVERALL REQUIRED SPACE: ~105 GB[/b][/*]
[/list]


[color=#5cbdcf][b][u][size=4]Pre-Installation[/size][/u][/b][/color]
[spoiler]
[list=1]
[*][url=https://support.cdprojektred.com/en/cyberpunk/pc/sp-technical/issue/2233/how-do-i-perform-a-clean-install-of-the-game]Perform a clean install of Cyberpunk 2077[/url] outside of Program Files.[/*]
[*][url=https://www.techpowerup.com/download/visual-c-redistributable-runtime-package-all-in-one/]Install Visual C++ Redistributables[/url] — run `install_all.bat` from the download.[/*]
[*]Right-click Cyberpunk 2077 in your Steam library > Properties > Updates tab > set to "Only update when I launch". From now on, [b]only launch the game through Mod Organizer 2.[/b][/*]
[*]Make sure [b]all DLC[/b] are installed.[/*]
[*]Install [url=https://store.steampowered.com/app/2060310/Cyberpunk_2077_REDmod/]REDmod (Free DLC)[/url] if you haven't already.[/*]
[/list]


[img]https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dc727531-5f72-4bb6-aa64-df340b48c1a3[/img]

[i]Make sure REDmod and Phantom Liberty both show as installed in Steam![/i][/spoiler]

[color=#5cbdcf][b][u][size=4]Installation[/size][/u][/b][/color]
[spoiler]
[list=1]
[*][b]Download [url=https://www.wabbajack.org]Wabbajack[/url][/b] and put it somewhere safe — not inside your Cyberpunk folder and not in a protected location like Program Files.
[i]Example:[/i] `D:\Wabbajack`
[/*]
[*][b]Download the Chrome & Blood `.wabbajack` file[/b] from the Files tab on this page and put it somewhere easy to find.
[i]Example:[/i] `D:\Wabbajack\Lists\Chrome & Blood.wabbajack`
[/*]
[*][b]Launch `Wabbajack.exe`[/b], click the browse icon on the left, then hit "install from disk" in the top-right corner and open the Chrome & Blood file.
[/*]
[*][b]Set your install and download folders.[/b]
[i]Examples:[/i]
Installation: `D:\Chrome & Blood`
Downloads: `D:\Chrome & Blood\downloads`

⚠️ Both folders need to be on the same drive as your Cyberpunk install, and [b]not[/b] inside the Cyberpunk folder.
[/*]
[*][b]Hit Install[/b] and let Wabbajack do its thing. This takes a while depending on your internet and hardware.
[/*]
[*][b]Once it's done,[/b] open your install folder and launch `ModOrganizer.exe`.
[/*]
[*]In MO2, make sure the profile is set to [b]Chrome & Blood[/b], then hit [b]Run[/b] in the top right.[/*]
[/list]
[/spoiler]

[color=#5cbdcf][b][u][size=4]Post-Installation: Antivirus[/size][/u][/b][/color]
[spoiler]
Antivirus software (especially BitDefender, Norton, Webroot) will cause problems with [url=https://stepmodifications.org/wiki/Guide:Mod_Organizer/Advanced]MO2's Virtual File System[/url]. You may need to fully remove third-party antivirus for this list to work properly. Windows Defender with smart browsing habits is enough.

If you're using Windows Defender, add folder exclusions:
[list=1]
[*]Open Windows Security[/*]
[*]Go to Virus & threat protection[/*]
[*]Click Manage settings[/*]
[*]Scroll to Exclusions > Add or remove exclusions[/*]
[*]Add your Chrome & Blood installation folder[/*]
[*](Optional) Also exclude ModOrganizer.exe and Cyberpunk2077.exe[/*]
[*]Disable any overlays — Steam overlay, Discord overlay, GPU software overlays, Xbox Game Bar, etc.[/*]
[/list]
[/spoiler]

[color=#5cbdcf][b][u][size=4]Updating the List[/size][/u][/b][/color]
[list=1]
[*]Download the latest `.wabbajack` file from the [b]Files[/b] tab on this page.[/*]
[*]Follow the installation steps above starting from step 2.[/*]
[*]Check the [url=https://qcargile.github.io/Chrome-Blood/changelog.html]changelog[/url] to see what changed.[/*]
[/list]


[color=#5cbdcf][b][u][size=4]Need Help?[/size][/u][/b][/color]
Check the [url=https://qcargile.github.io/Chrome-Blood/faq.html]FAQ[/url] first — it covers backups, updates, performance, and the most common questions. Then join the [url=https://discord.gg/U65Nhdcns8]Chrome & Blood Discord[/url] for support with either install method. We're around to help troubleshoot, answer questions, or just talk shop.
